  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "We are debugging a retry failure with reset. Here is what is happening\r\n- The request is sent to Server Envoy. The local service returned 503. \r\n- The Server Envoy Stats `upstream_rq_5xx` is incremented.\r\n- The Server Envoy sends back http status code `200` and gRPC status code `Unavailable`\r\n- The Client Envoy retries the request `upstream_rq_retry` is incremented for the Cluster\r\n- The retry fails with upstream reset. No 5xx is incremented on the Client Envoy.\r\n- The actual client is returned with `UnAvailable` with message `upstream connect error or disconnect/reset before headers`.\r\n \r\nLooking at the code in router.cc, I suspect it is getting in to this if condition. \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/cdcdfa6914f88b537122ed039fd0de5f78c0f209/source/common/router/router.cc#L575\r\n\r\nI am not able to confirm it because the host level stat is updated. AFAIK, host level stats does not go stat sinks and the Envoy in question has been restarted - so we lost the host level stats. There are no other stats on Client I could use to confirm why the retry failed - any other stats could help me figure that out?\r\n\r\nIs there a specific reason why this stat is only incremented at host level but not at cluster level?\r\n",
